✅Learned how to use the git restore command with the --staged option to unstage changes from the staging area. Useful when you accidentally stage changes that you don't want to commit. #GitUnstage
✅Learned how to use the git restore command to unmodify changes in the working directory. Useful when you want to undo changes made to a file before it was staged. #GitUnmodify

✅Learned how to use the git checkout command with the -- file option to discard changes to a specific file. Useful when you want to discard changes to a specific file but keep changes to other files. #GitDiscardChanges
✅Learned how to use the ^ and ~ symbols to reference commits relative to HEAD. Useful when you need to refer to a previous commit without specifying its hash. #GitRelativeRefs
✅Learned how to use the git checkout command to reattach our detached HEAD to a specific branch. Useful when you accidentally detach the HEAD from the branch. #GitReattachHEAD
